nd sixty seven nonbaháí iranian academics writers artists journalists and activists from  countries including iran who signed an open letter of apology posted to iraniancom and stating they were ashamed and pledging their support in baháís achieving the rights detailed in the universal declaration of human rights for the baháís in iran see persecution of baháís prior to the  uk general election he was one of several celebrities who endorsed the parliamentary candidacy of the green partys caroline lucas see alsoedit ilısu dam campaign robert newman southeastern anatolia project corporate crime serious organised crime and police act  see protests near parliament section notesedit  a b c d phil daoust  january  stand up and be taunted the guardian retrieved    biography markthomasinfocom archived from the original on  retrieved    comedian mark thomas my dad was a rightwing thatcher supporter metrocouk  october  retrieved  april    cornock david  october  waleswestminster newslog bbc news online retrieved  may    a b jacques adam  october  mark thomas interview the socialactivist comedian talks opera charity shops and nicholas soames the independent london retrieved  may    james clasper the london line  may  taking the fizz out of cokes image spinwatch retrieved    boycott killer coke colombia action network  september  retrieved    comedian praised over weapons trade yahoo news  august  archived from the original on  may  retrieved    parliament protesters fight ban bbc news  august  retrieved    naomi gallichan  november  review mark thomas the royal court liverpool liverpoolcom archived from the original on  retrieved    mark thomas  october  mark thomas on demonstrating near the houses of parliament the guardian retrieved    mark thomas is awarded honorary doctorate by bradford university mark thomas info retrieved    update on thatcher funeral policy mark thomas info retrieved    the guardian  april  comedian mark thomas wins £ over police search  comedian mark t